==Translingual==
===Letter===
'''ᚁ'''

# the [[ogham]] letter ''beith''
#: ᚁ (''beith'') corresponds to the latin letter ''[[B]]''. It is the first letter in the "B" group ([[Old Irish]]: ''Aicme Beithe''), the first family of ogham letters. The following letter is [[ᚂ]] (''luis'').

===Character===
#ᚁ is often used online when text cannot be displayed by a computer and/or browser. For example, on non-English websites, some computers/browsers display ᚁ because they cannot display the foreign-language characters

